sql:
SELECT AVG(session_time) AS avg_session_time
FROM app_usage
WHERE push_notifications = 0;

external_knowledge:
- "engaged with the app" refers to users who have sessions with push notifications or in-app messages enabled;
- "getting content recommendations" means users have received at least one content recommendation;
- "making purchases" means users have made at least one in-app purchase.

sql:
SELECT MAX(average_session_time) 
FROM app_usage 
WHERE push_notifications = 1 AND in_app_messages = 0;

SELECT user_id, total_sessions, average_session_time
FROM app_usage
WHERE in_app_purchases > 0 AND push_notifications = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'push_notifications' indicates whether a user has push notifications enabled (1) or disabled (0);
- 'session_time' is the duration a user spends in a single session on the app;
- 'in_app_purchases' refers to the number of purchases made by the user within the app.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(id) 
FROM in_app_messages 
WHERE read_at IS NOT NULL;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM in_app_messages 
WHERE user_id IN (SELECT user_id FROM app_usage WHERE push_notifications = 1);

